Goal.

Create a connect 4 system that can be played by a user against and automated opponent or that can be played by two automated players. 


Done		User is able to set the dimensions of the board at start		Done
To Do 		User can choose moves 										
Status		Game can detect horizontal connect4s 
Status		Game can detect vertical connect4s 
Status		Game handles scenarios where sequential pieces are not wins (spillover)
Status		User can select number of pieces to connect to win
Status		Game draws a graphical representation of game 
Status		Game can conect to Arduino serially 
Status		Arduino can accept moves from Game and display on matrix 
Status		Game tracks the progression of the game 
Status		Game knows spaces that are occupied 
Status		Game knows which moves are legal 
Status		Game outputs information as each turn is made 
Status		User can select if board is drawn at endTurn
Status		User can input how many games to play in series
Status		Game verifies user input before proceeding on a series 
Status		Game can track the outcome of every game in a series 
Status		Game displays winner and relevant information 
Status		Game ends the current game following a win detect 
Status 		Game can clear memory and begin a new game (if a series is set by User)
Status		Enable Reinforcement Learning
Status		Define conditions and rewards
Status		Define what constitutes a single Step (both player completes a turn)
Status		Game assigns points to each player for each game in a series
Status		Game has at least 2 levels of output messages one and user can select
Status		One level of output contains highly granular debug information
Status		Game messages should have some formatting for presentation
